HEADWORD: Drupe
<hw>Drupe</hw> <pr>(dr⟦udd⟧p)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>drupe</ets>, L. <ets>drupa</ets> an overripe, wrinkled olive, fr.
Gr. <grk>dry`ppa</grk>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A fruit consisting
of pulpy, coriaceous, or fibrous exocarp, without valves, containing a
nut or stone with a kernel. The exocarp is succulent in the plum,
cherry, apricot, peach, etc.; dry and subcoriaceous in the almond; and
fibrous in the cocoanut.</def></p>

